## Phase 12: Order Management System

### Order Lifecycle States

| State | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| PENDING_NEW | Created, not yet submitted |
| NEW | Submitted to venue |
| PARTIALLY_FILLED | Partial execution |
| FILLED | Complete execution |
| PENDING_CANCEL | Cancel requested |
| CANCELLED | Successfully cancelled |
| REJECTED | Venue rejected |
| EXPIRED | Time expired |

### Order Entity

```python
@dataclass
class Order:
    order_id: str
    client_order_id: str
    authorization_id: str
    symbol: str
    side: str
    order_type: OrderType
    quantity: float
    limit_price: Optional[float]
    
    state: OrderState = OrderState.PENDING_NEW
    filled_quantity: float = 0.0
    avg_fill_price: float = 0.0
    
    state_history: List[Dict] = field(default_factory=list)
```

### Key OMS Operations

```python
class OrderManagementSystem:
    async def create_order(self, authorization_id, symbol, side, quantity, ...) -> Order:
        """Create order from authorization"""
    
    async def submit_order(self, order_id: str) -> Order:
        """Submit to execution engine"""
    
    async def record_fill(self, order_id, fill_qty, fill_price) -> Order:
        """Record execution fill"""
    
    async def cancel_order(self, order_id, reason) -> Order:
        """Request cancellation"""
    
    async def get_working_orders(self) -> List[Order]:
        """Get all active orders"""
